OL,6,FThe pair argued when they returned
OL,7,Fhome to their beauty spot cottage on
OL,8,Fthe Gower Peninsula where "doting
OL,9,Fgranny" Mrs Clarke struck her husband
OL,10,Fwith a picture frame and cup of tea.
OL,11,FProsecutor Michael Jones KC said four
OL,12,Fdays after arriving home father-of-
OL,13,Ffour Clarke texted family members
OL,14,Ftelling them: "I love you".JHe then
OL,15,Fset off with his wife for a drive "to
OL,16,Fthe beach".JBut during the journey
OL,17,FClarke stopped the car and struck his
OL,18,Fwife several times in the head with a
OL,19,Flump hammer, throwing paraffin on her
OL,20,Fbody and setting her on fire.
